The Inter-Party Advisory Council (IPAC) has called on the Niger State Independent Electoral Commission (NSIEC) to announce the result of the election into Tafa local government council to douse tension in the area Last week the NSIEC has announced that the returning officer dissappeared with the result and thus has canceled the result with protest trailing the decision, IPAC at the end of its meeting to review the conduct of the election said the commission should have gone ahead to announce the outcome since collation was done at the ward levels. IPAC in its resolution signed by the secretary, Mohammed Bello Maikujeri. stated that “Council as an umbrella body of all registered political parties in the state and major stakeholder in politics is jealously guided by the interest of political parties but believe that the peaceful coexistence of the people of Niger State is equally paramount.”